<https://www.gov.uk/government/people/simon-webb> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://schema.org/WebPage> .
_:N40a9a5b766444ffbbf00892ba2b9474a <http://schema.org/description> "<p>Simon Webb CBE, FICE, specialises in major programmes and strategic change.</p>\n\n<p>An Executive Director at Nichols Group, he has led their work on nuclear decommissioning and warships for the last 10 years, at sites in England, Scotland and Wales. Simon was a non-executive Director of the Major Projects Association from 2010 to 2021. He is a member of the United Nations Economic Commission for Europe’s Group of Experts on Risk Management in Regulatory Systems.</p>\n\n<p>Previously Simon was a Director-General in the Department of Transport and the Ministry of Defence, responsible for major projects and security policy.</p>\n\n<p>Appointed: January 2022<br>Term ends: January 2025</p>\n\n<p>Reappointed: January 2025<br>Term ends: January 2029</p>\n" .
